<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Crystal Haze7 (Windows 7 style)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=4659&amp;p=19968#p19968"><![CDATA[
One thing. <br />If you look at the picture, there is a programs flyout link on the right side of the menu.<br />If you are wondering about it. Usually Win7 style has the menu on the left.<br />Way back two years ago, I was using a toolbar menu for Win8, as it was hard to adapt at first to the start screen.<br />It was different though, as it combined the all users and single user together to make a menu folder. I got the info from <br />either Win8 or Win7 forum. I still have the folder on my drive. File folder(.{7BE9D83C-A729-4D97-B5A7-1B7313C39E0A})<br />Of course, then I found Classic Shell Menu. <br />So much better.<img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_e_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=856">juniper7</a> — Tue Jun 23, 2015 12:00 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
